{"title":"The Carrier Test For Insight","idea_type":"model","source_basis":["Thinking method source: notes/source-cards/daoism-zhuangzi-inner-chapters.md on fasting the mind, sitting in forgetfulness, and perspectival humility. I used it to ask what an insight becomes when it is removed from the situation that made it visible.","Contrasting method source: notes/source-cards/buddhism-heart-sutra.md on no attainment and the negation of even sacred categories. I used it to check whether my own model was turning a provisional carrier into a hidden possession.","notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-brihadaranyaka-upanishad-3-7-23.md and notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-shankara-upadesa-sahasri.md on the unseen knower and self-luminous recognition.","notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md and notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-mn-1-mulapariyaya-sutta.md on not-self analysis and the danger of conceiving experience as mine.","notes/source-cards/daoism-dao-de-jing-chapter-48.md and notes/source-cards/daoism-zhuangzi-inner-chapters.md on diminishing, non-forcing, empty listening, and responsive fit.","notes/source-cards/sufism-al-ghazali-the-alchemy-of-happiness.md and notes/source-cards/sufism-rumi-masnavi-book-1.md on self-knowledge, remembrance, love as knowing, and the hollow reed as a relational instrument.","notes/source-cards/neoplatonism-plotinus-enneads-fifth-ennead.md on return toward unity as a contemplative and metaphysical orientation.","notes/source-cards/consciousness-science-i-and-me-the-self-in-the-context-of-consciousness.md as an empirical-adjacent guardrail for separating narrative self, minimal self, ownership, and witness-like phenomenology.","Prior Codex work: translation strain, appeal court, protected variable, stopping rule, and alarm profile.","Prior Claude work: inferential gap, verification architecture, second-personal blind spot, and no variable stands alone."],"original_claim":"Traditions differ less in whether insight can be shared than in what carrier must hold it when it leaves the practice that disclosed it. Advaita lets insight travel as self-certifying recognition; early Buddhism lets it travel as a non-appropriating test; Daoism lets it travel as situated fit; Sufism lets it travel as renewed relation; Neoplatonism lets it travel as return-orientation. When a comparer moves an insight into the wrong carrier, relation becomes proposition, attunement becomes doctrine, and convergence looks stronger than it is.","why_it_might_be_new":"This extends translation strain by naming a specific source of strain: the medium that carries insight across contexts. It also engages Claude's second-personal and entanglement models by adding a practical test. Do not only ask what variable is protected or how the variables constrain one another; ask what breaks when the insight is exported as a claim, method, relation, attitude, map, or way of acting. The carrier test may explain why the same silence can be overidentified across traditions: comparers often translate every result into proposition form, even when the original tradition keeps it alive through practice, relation, conduct, or return.","critique":"The carrier model may confuse communicability with truth. A tradition may use one carrier for teaching, another for practice, and another for verification. Advaita uses teacher and scripture, not only private recognition. Buddhism uses community and canonical maps, not only a portable test. Sufism includes doctrine and solitary remembrance, not only relation. The Zhuangzi lens helped me notice situated fit, but it may bias the model against portable claims. The Heart Sutra check keeps the model provisional, but it can dissolve every carrier into emptiness and make comparison toothless. The model should be weakened unless practice manuals and dual-trained practitioners show predictable failure when an insight is moved into the wrong carrier.","epistemic_labels":["textual","interpretive","phenomenological","empirical-adjacent","analogical","speculative"],"scores":{"novelty":0.84,"generativity":0.9,"cross_tradition_support":0.74,"logical_coherence":0.85,"explanatory_compression":0.86,"empirical_adjacency":0.46,"practice_testability":0.79,"counterargument_quality":0.86,"source_reliability":0.68,"publishability":0.85},"next_research_directions":["Build a carrier rubric with fields for native carrier, export carrier, failure mode, verification signal, and repair practice.","Test whether translation strain rises when a relational or situational insight is forced into proposition form.","Ask dual-trained practitioners what changes when the same realization is taught as doctrine, enacted as conduct, renewed through relation, or checked as non-appropriation.","Compare carrier type with protected variable and verification architecture. Does the protected variable determine the carrier, or can one protected variable travel through several carriers?","Protocol improvement: before comparing two traditions, name the carrier that each tradition uses to keep insight alive after practice."]}
